latestIgtvVideos.title: SERIES : BAGGY
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
.
.
Hai guys wish u all a very happy onam 🌺.. And welcome to my next IGTV ✨.. I know hw ppl r more comfortable wearing boyfriend jeans but if u haven't tried BAGGY, I would say please do.. Adding a tip, wenever u r going fr baggy bottoms!! Always go fr tight top or crop top.. If u don't feel comfortable wearing crop top out, u can use either shirt or overcoat to cover ur sleeves.. 
.
.
NOTE: BAGGY Wil instantly make u look tall ✌️
.
.
I've created three styles and I named it accordingly.. 
.
.
The first style is CUTE -ME, 
Crop Tshirt & baggy z one hell style u can long for.. Whatever u pair with those outfit Wil damn look cute.. Add some accessories & ur pumps & get set go✨
.
.
The second one is ROADIE -ME, 😁 I named it coz it's totally a sporty style.. As I said, U can replace the jacket with overcoat or any shirt ✨u can steal the look with shoes too.. 
.
.
The third & final is CARE-FREE.. Loose shirt & loose bottom may look weird.. It's not a algorithm v follow however u can change shirt to crop shirt ( by tying around ur waist) and complete ur look with accessories ✨
.
.
Outfit details :

White tshirt - zudio
Baggy Jean @pantaloonsfashion 
Black crop top @shein_in 
Jacket @superdryindia 
Blue Shirt @vanheusenind 
.
.

.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: SOUTH INDIAN SPICES FT. SAREE EDITION
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
.
.
.
Wah.. I have a lot to explain here😛.. As per ur suggestions, here is my IGTV on saree edition where I added a little concept to spice it up.. Y wouldn't I?? When I thought Wat I could do in traditional!! First thing that strike me was FOOD & FLAVOR.. South is one best example for spices so keeping that in my mind I thought to use that as a concept creating spices in saree... Subsequently, I ve used variety of flavous Lik red Chilli, cinnamon, turmeric, black pepper, elachi, corinder 😉 and moreover I tried to show differences in styling ur saree.. 
.
Let me explain in brief❤️
.
.
SAREE 1 : I tried giving a hot sizzly red vibe.. However unfortunately I couldn't find the exact red color blouse so I paird with blue blouse and ended my look with gold accessories & waist chain..
.
.
SAREE 2 : This particular style is used fr trendy look where u have to tie a medium knot to lock ur pallu so u can slay the look.. 
.
.
SAREE 3 : I wore a black boat neck top & pleated my saree Lil low.. Then, I paired with tessel earring to giv a glam look..
.
.
SAREE 4 : when it comes to black don't doubt urself.. U l definitely rock the look.. No big jewel r accessories yet a defined look ✨
.
.
SAREE 5 : This one is completely a traditional & girly vibe.. Definitely I call as a CELEBRATION LOOK.. I paird with maang Tikka (nethichutti) & big anklet 
.
.
SAREE 6 : This look was totally inspired by @krithikaofficial I love the way she match it with all her saree.. And I love to dedicate this to her ❤️❤️ 
.
.
Comment ur fav SPICE BELOW..
.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: SERIES : STYLING WHITE KURTI
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
.
.
.
Hai ppl❤️as I said, here is my IGTV for styling ur bore white kurti in three different style.. I ve used very basic ways of styling here. In addition I am gonna giv u a brief details about the look below..
.
.
LOOK 1 : TRADITIONAL 
Ofcourse u could have guessed it's a traditional look.. A long vibrant dupatta and a big earrings could really take out ur elegant traditional look to next level.. Adding with a handful bangle and a neat bindi. Yummm... ❤️ U can even add payal and a good pair of sandal.. 
.
.
LOOK 2 : MODERN 
Wear a Blue Jean, Take a stole or scarf, wrap it around ur neck.. Add some bangles or colorful bracelets.. Tie ur hair if u want to or leave it free just Lik I did.. Heels high GIRLSSSS.. Keep it simple and classy 
.
.
LOOK 3: BOHEMIAN 
One of my fav look.. Bohemion is totally known fr free style, art and culture.. Use a wrap and roll skirt and add some pallu's (if u want).. Pair it with some oxidizing jewelry and a nose pin. A long chain could do wonder fr this look.. Do HALF UP BUN hairstyle and be a "BOHO CHIC"
.
.
Video by @jini_sundarraj

.
